{{version030}}
{{flavour|Releases a fast, gas-filled floating spore. After seeking out its foe, the spore will explode, damaging anything caught in the blast and further confusing living creatures.}}

'''Sporulate''' is a monsters-only spell which spawns [[ballistomycete spore]]s to attack and confuse living monsters. Ballistomycete spores explode on contact or on death in a 3x3 square, dealing <code>3d(5 + [[HD]])</code> (i.e. 3d(6 + [[Invocations]])) damage and [[confusing]] any [[unbreathing|breathing]] creatures.

{{monsters with spell}}

==History==
*Prior to [[0.24]], ballistomycetes used spores to reproduce. They dealt a flat 3d15 damage and had a radius of 2 (5x5 explosion).

[[Category:Monster spells]]
